VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT (?i)export\s+(?:PASSWORD|SECRET|API_KEY|APIKEY|TOKEN|ACCESS_KEY|PRIVATE_KEY|AUTH_TOKEN|PASSWD|CREDENTIAL)\s*=\s*\S
WHEN EXPR MISSING:\$\(|example|sample|test|placeholder
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects hardcoded credentials or secrets assigned to environment variable exports in Makefiles and shell scripts.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Hardcoded Secrets in Environment Variables.
